# Code of Conduct

## Welcome to the Project!

This Code of Conduct outlines expectations for all contributors and participants in this GitHub repository. Our goal is to foster an open and welcoming environment where everyone feels respected and valued.

---

## üí° Our Standards

We are committed to providing a friendly, safe, and inclusive environment for all, regardless of:

- Gender identity and expression  
- Age  
- Disability  
- Ethnicity or race  
- Level of experience  
- Nationality  
- Personal appearance  
- Religion or belief  
- Sexual orientation  

### ‚úÖ Examples of acceptable behavior:

- Respectful and constructive communication  
- Active collaboration and teamwork  
- Offering and receiving helpful feedback  
- Being open to different opinions and experiences  

### ‚ùå Unacceptable behavior includes:

- Offensive or disrespectful comments  
- Discrimination or harassment of any kind  
- Threats or violent language  
- Sharing others‚Äô private information without consent  
- Disruptive or destructive behavior

---

## üì¢ Reporting Issues

If you observe or experience any behavior that violates this Code of Conduct, please report it by opening a private issue or emailing the maintainer(s) of this repository.

All reports will be handled confidentially and professionally.

---

## üõ† Enforcement

The maintainers of this project reserve the right to:

- Remove comments, commits, code, or other contributions that do not align with this Code of Conduct.  
- Ban temporarily or permanently any contributor whose behavior is deemed inappropriate, threatening, or harmful.

---

## ü§ù Let‚Äôs build something great, together!

We encourage you to contribute and be a part of this community while helping us keep it respectful and inclusive.

